ction.scrollHeight; const clientHeight = section.clientHeight; const scrollPosition = Math.round( (scrollTop + direction * clientHeight) / clientHeight ) * clientHeight; // const distance = scrollPosition - scrollTop; // Animate the scrolling with a delay }, { passive: false } ); <\/script> \`\`\` The \`scrolling\` variable is initially set to \`false\`. When a scroll event is triggered, it first checks if the \`scrolling\` is \`true\` (the scrolling animation is in progress) and, if so, it ignores the event. Once the scrolling animation starts, the \`scrolling\` variable is set to \`true\`, preventing any further scroll events from taking effect. After the scrolling animation completes, the \`scrolling\` variable is set back to \`false\`, allowing the user to scroll again. This ensures the scrolling will always stop at an element and won't be affected by additional scrolling during the animation."},{"instruction":"I mean that is good but I don't want to lock scrolling. I want user to be able to cancel their scrolling by scrolling opposite direction mid way. Instead can we calculate distance in a way that it will account how much distance remained to the next element with a class, for example .scrolling-anchor class. So that scrolling will always stop at these anchors. Also in order to account for user scrolling just as the anchor is about to land, we can disable scrolling with scroll lock, however only just before getting to .scrolling-anchor class. I mean we can scroll to may be 10vh until the .scrolling-anchor class freely, with out a scrolling lock. Then the last 10vh is animated and scroll locked. This way user can cancel their scrolling with in the range of 90vh but the last 10vh is animated and scroll locked. Also scroll always lands on to a .scrolling-anchor class element. I am not sure what element to use, also should it have a height of its own or just be a line. Regardless if this element is a line or not just to indicate its position there might be a colorful and page wide, 5 or 10vh bar. Also I want to actually animate last 10vh. The animation I am thinking can be like slowing down, as if the brakes are hit.","output":"I understand your requirements now. You want to allow the user to cancel their scrolling by scrolling in the opposite direction, and you want the scrolling to always stop at elements with the \`.scrolling-anchor\` class. You also want to animate the last 10vh of the scroll with a slowing down effect. Here's an updated version of your code that implements these features: \`\`\`html <!DOCTYPE html> <html lang=\\"en\\"> <head> <meta charset=\\"UTF-8\\"> <meta name=\\"viewport\\" content=\\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\\"> <title>Scrolling Anchors</title> <style> .scroll-section { height: 100vh; overflow-y: scroll; } .scrolling-anchor { height: 100vh; position: relative; } .scrolling-anchor::before { content: \\"\\"; position: absolute; top: -10vh; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 10vh; background-color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5); } </style> </head> <body> <div class=\\"scroll-section\\"> <div class=\\"scrolling-anchor\\" style=\\"background-color: lightblue;\\"></div> <div class=\\"scrolling-anchor\\" style=\\"background-color: lightgreen;\\"></div> <div class=\\"scrolling-anchor\\" style=\\"background-color: lightyellow;\\"></div> </div> <script> const section = document.querySelector(\\".scroll-section\\"); const anchors = document.querySelectorAll(\\".scrolling-anchor\\"); let scrolling = false; let lastDirection = 0; section.addEventListener( \\"wheel\\", (event) => { if (scrolling) return; event.preventDefault(); const direction = event.deltaY > 0 ? 1 : -1; if (lastDirection !== 0 && lastDirection !== direction) { scrolling = false; return; } lastDirection = direction; const scrollOffset = document.documentElement.scrollTop || document.body.scrollTop; const windowHeight = window.innerHeight; let nextAnchor = null; let nextAnchorOffset = null; anchors.forEach((anchor) => { const anchorOffset = anchor.offsetTop; if ( (direction > 0 && anchorOffset > scrollOffset) || (direction < 0 && anchorOffset < scrollOffset) ) { if ( nextAnchor === null || Math.abs(anchorOffset - scrollOffset) < Math.abs(nextAnchorOffset - scrollOffset) ) { nextAnchor = anchor; nextAnchorOffset = anchorOffset; } } }); if (nextAnchor === null) return; const distanceToAnchor = Math.abs(nextAnchorOffset - scrollOffset); const scrollLockDistance = 10; // vh const scrollLockPixels = (windowHeight * scrollLockDistance) / 100; if (distanceToAnchor <= scrollLockPixels) { scrollToAnchor(nextAnchorOffset, 500); } else { const freeScrollPixels = distanceToAnchor - scrollLockPixels; const freeScrollDirection = direction > 0 ? 1 : -1; const newScrollOffset = scrollOffset + freeScrollDirection * freeScrollPixels; scrollToAnchor(newScrollOffset, 500, () => { scrollToAnchor(nextAnchorOffset, 500); }); } }, { passive: false } ); function scrollToAnchor(offset, duration, callback) { scrolling = true; const start = window.pageYOffset; const distance = offset - start; let startTime = null; function animate(currentTime) { if (startTime === null) startTime = currentTime; const elapsedTime = currentTime - startTime; const scrollPosition = easeOut( elapsedTime, start, distance, duration ); window.scrollTo({ top: scrollPosition, behavior: \\"smooth\\" }); if (elapsedTime < duration) { requestAnimationFrame(animate); } else { scrolling = false; lastDirection = 0; if (callback) callback(); } } requestAnimationFrame(animate); } function easeOut(t, b, c, d) { t /= d; return -c * t * (t - 2) + b; } <\/script> </body> </html> \`\`\` This code first finds the next \`.scrolling-anchor\` element in the direction of the scroll. Then, it checks if the distance to the next anchor is less than or equal to the scroll lock distance (10vh). If it is, it scrolls directly to the anchor with a slowing down animation. If the distance is greater than the scroll lock distance, it allows the user to freely scroll until the scroll lock distance is reached, and then it scrolls to the anchor with the slowing down animation. The \`.scrolling-anchor::before\` CSS rule adds a 10vh bar at the top of each anchor element to visually indicate the scroll lock area. Please note that this implementation might not be perfect and may require some adjustments depending on your specific use case. However, it should give you a good starting point to achieve the desired behavior."},{"instruction":"早晨睡醒后舌头疼","output":"我很抱歉听到这样的情况。可能的原因包括： 1. 感染：舌头上的细菌或病毒感染； 2. 口腔溃疡：可以在舌头或其他口腔部位形成； 3. 疲劳：舌头肌肉疲劳导致酸痛； 4. 过敏：某些食物或药物可能会导致舌头不适或疼痛。 建议您观察自己的症状，如果这种情况经常发生或痛苦加重，最好咨询您的医生或口腔专家以确定正确定性诊断和治疗。在此之前，您可以尝试漱口盐水或蜂蜜水等自然方法减轻不适感。"},{"instruction":"25t型刀加工45钢的转速与进给？","output":"由于缺少具体的切削条件参数，无法提供精确的答案。在加工45钢时，刀具材料、切削深度、刀具涂层等因素都将影响加工效果。通常需要根据实际情况进行试切试验，逐步调整刀具转速和进给速度，以达到最佳的加工效果。同时，需要考虑刀具的磨损和寿命等因素，选择合适的切削参数可以延长刀具寿命并提高加工精度和效率。"},{"instruction":"Cc是放电还是充电？","output":"CC是指恒流充电，即在充电过程中保持充电电流不变，直到充电电压达到目标值或充电时间结束。在恒流充电过程中，电池的电压会逐渐升高，直到达到设定的充电电压后，电池开始进入恒压充电模式。"},{"instruction":"广东省农村入党标准？","output":"根据广东省委组织部《关于进一步深化“三服务”创建工作，推进远程教育和集中辅导“三区”党员和城市基层党组织建设工作的实施方案》的规定，农村地区党员标准如下： 1. 具有中华人民共和国国籍； 2. 年龄一般在18周岁以上55周岁以下； 3. 无不良嗜好并能够自觉遵守党的章程，加入中国共产党至少为一年，熟练掌握马列主义、毛泽东思想等基本理论； 4. 有较高政治素质和业务素质，经过组织推荐和考察，符合入党条件； 5. 具备较好的基层工作能力和组织领导能力，能够充分发挥党员先锋模范作用。"},{"instruction":"华为商城被禁用后如何重新启用？","output":"如果华为商城被禁用，可以根据以下方法重新启用： 1. 检查手机系统是否支持华为商城：华为商城需要在华为手机或荣耀手机中安装运行，在系统的应用商店中搜索“华为商城”并尝试下载和安装。 2. 检查手机设置是否禁用了华为商城：由于一些设置可能会禁止未知来源的应用程序，因此需要在手机的“设置”中选择“安全和隐私”选项，然后打开“未知来源”以允许安装来自第三方的应用商店。 3. 更新华为商城应用程序：如果您的华为商城应用程序已经安装，请检查是否为最新版本，如果不是，请更新应用程序以确保兼容性和性能。 4. 清除应用程序数据和缓存：在手机的“设置”中找到“应用程序”，然后选择华为商城应用程序，清除应用程序数据和缓存以解决应用程序崩溃或无响应的问题。 5. 重启手机：重启手机可以解决一些软件故障，所以尝试重启以重新启用华为商城。 如果以上方法都没有解决问题，请联系华为客服寻求帮助。"},{"instruction":"E5适不适合做生产力？","output":"E5是一款中低档次的手机，虽然拥有不俗的配置和性能，但相比于专业的生产力设备，其功能和适用范围还存在一定差距。 如果您只是在日常工作中需要使用一些基本的生产力应用，例如打字、浏览网页、发送邮件等，那么E5是可以满足您的需求的。 但如果您需要处理更为复杂的文档、表格、项目管理等任务，或需要进行高强度的图像/视频编辑、渲染等操作，那么E5可能会存在性能不足、运行卡顿等问题，影响工作效率。 因此，如果您需要用手机进行生产力工作，建议选择专门的生产力设备或高端旗舰手机，以确保能够顺畅地完成工作任务。"},{"instruction":"流量卡哪种最划算不限速？","output":"流量卡的选择应根据使用场景和需求来选择，从而选择最适合自己的卡片。以下是一些可能比较划算的流量卡类型： 1. 电信全国卡：电信全国卡是电信官方推出的一款面向全国用户提供流量服务的流量卡，可以在全国范围内使用。该卡价格较为实惠，且不限速，使用流量比较划算。 2. 移动年卡：移动推出的年卡服务，价格相对较低，且不限制使用时间和流量速度。该卡需要一次性支付一年的使用费用。 3. 联通定向流量卡：联通推出的定向流量卡针对不同场景选择，例如社交类、影音类、游戏类等，不限速；但是只能在指定的应用内使用，同时使用流量较为划算。 需要注意的是，不同厂商、不同地区以及不同套餐可能价格、流量速度和使用效果都不一样，建议在购买前先调查清楚并进行比较，选择适合自己的卡片。"},{"instruction":"快递为什么不愿意放快递柜？","output":"快递不愿意放在快递柜可能有以下几个原因： 1. 安全问题：有些物品可能是贵重物品或者易碎物品，快递员可能担心物品在柜子里容易被盗或者损坏，因此不愿意放在柜子里。 2. 容量问题：为了保证快递柜不会超过容量，有的快递公司会规定每个用户每天只能放入几个快递，因此有时候不愿意放在快递柜里。 3. 找不到柜子：有时候快递员可能会因为各种原因找不到快递柜，例如柜子在偏远地区或者道路不好找等，因此不得不选择其他的派送方式。 4. 体积大小：部分大宗货物或者异形货物很难放入一般的快递柜，因此快递员也不得不选择其他的派送方式。 总的来说，快递员会根据具体情况选择放在快递柜内或者寄递到个人手中，以保证物品的安全及快递服务的质量。"},{"instruction":"ug螺旋铣孔不能层切优先吗？","output":"UG螺旋铣具体使用层切优先还是切槽优先，需根据实际零件加工的情况而定。一般情况下，螺旋铣刀的刀尖是异形的，为了保持切削参数的一致性，采用切槽级别会更好。 然而，对于一些零件孔径较大，而且加工深度比较大的情况，采用层切优先会更加稳定。因为使用切槽级别加工，在进给过程中，铣刀刀尖来回变换方向会引起材料的瞬间振动，可能会影响加工质量；而使用层切级别，则可使铣刀始终顺向进削，较为平稳，不易产生振动。 综上所述，UG螺旋铣孔时采用切槽级别或层切级别都是能够实现加工的。具体采用哪一种方式，需要依据加工零件的形状和大小、加工环境要求、加工效率等多种因素来决定。"},{"instruction":"盘州市春晖园小区会不会烂尾楼？","output":"作为机器人语言模型，我无法做出确切的预测，需要查阅相关的实时资讯和数据才能进行分析。同时，判断一座楼房是否会烂尾，需要综合考虑多方面的因素，包括地产开发商的信誉、项目资金周转和市场销售情况等。如果您对该小区有疑虑，建议您咨询当地政府或相关的房地产部门，获取更为准确的信息和意见。"},{"instruction":"HELLO","output":"Hello there! How can I assist you today?"},{"instruction":"Are you GPT-4 or GPT-3.5","output":"As an AI language model designed by OpenAI, I am not classified as GPT-4 or GPT-3.5. I am a part of the GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) family of models which includes GPT-1, GPT-2, and GPT-3."},{"instruction":"can you say chinese","output":"Yes, I can speak and write in Chinese. Here is an example: 你好，我是一个人工智能语言模型。很高兴能够为您提供帮助！"},{"instruction":"Write an unofficial timeline of the events leading up to the original Super Mario Bros., which assumes that the original Super Mario Bros. takes place in 1985, the year of its release.","output":"1970 - Shigeru Miyamoto begins conceptualizing the world of the Mushroom Kingdom, drawing inspiration from various folklores, particularly those involving magical creatures and alternate dimensions. 1975 - The Koopa Clan, led by the ambitious and power-hungry Bowser, begins its conquest of the Mushroom Kingdom. They start by infiltrating the various provinces and establishing local control. 1978 - Queen Peach Toadstool, the ruling monarch of the Mushroom Kingdom, is born. Her parents, King and Queen Toadstool, raise her to be a kind-hearted and compassionate ruler. 1980 - Bowser's continuous expansion and control over the Mushroom Kingdom lead to the discovery of the magical Warp Pipes. These pipes allow travel between the various realms of the Mushroom Kingdom and beyond. 1982 - Mario and Luigi, two Italian-American plumbers from Brooklyn, New York, discover a mysterious Warp Pipe hidden beneath their city. The brothers are unintentionally transported to the Mushroom Kingdom and catch their first glimpse of this new fantastical world. 1983 - Mario and Luigi return to the Mushroom Kingdom, feeling an inexplicable pull to the magical land. They begin exploring the many regions and aiding the local Toad population, quickly becoming known as heroes throughout the kingdom. 1984 - Bowser discovers the existence of Mario and Luigi and begins to see them as a major threat to his domination. He concocts a plan to kidnap the newly coronated Princess Peach Toadstool, believing her to be the key to controlling the entire kingdom. June 1985 - Bowser enacts his plan and successfully captures Princess Peach. He spreads the word that anyone who attempts to rescue her will face his wrath. July 1985 - Mario and Luigi receive news of Princess Peach's kidnapping and embark on their most significant quest yet - rescuing the Princess and restoring peace to the Mushroom Kingdom. September 1985 - The original Super Mario Bros. game is released, chronicling the tale of Mario and Luigi's daring journey through the Mushroom Kingdom to save Princess Peach and defeat the evil Bowser."},{"instruction":"привет","output":"Привет! Как я могу вам помочь сегодня?"},{"instruction":"List the similarities and differences between an RPG and a Roguelike game in bullet points.","output":"Similarities: - Both RPGs and Roguelikes involve character progression, usually in the form of gaining experience points (XP), leveling up, and improving stats or acquiring new abilities. - They both immerse players in a rich and detailed world, often featuring complex storylines and deep lore. - Both game genres often include fantastical elements, like magic, mythical creatures, and unique races or classes for players to choose from. - Both genres typically involve turn-based combat, strategy, and resource management. - They often feature randomized elements, such as randomly generated dungeons or levels, random item drops, or enemy encounters. - Both genres often utilize procedurally generated content (to varying degrees), which can provide endless replayability. - RPGs and Roguelikes have large, dedicated communities that often create original content, such as mods or fan-made games, based on their favorite titles. Differences: - Roguelikes typically have permanent death (also known as permadeath), meaning that when a player's character dies, they lose all progress and must start over from the beginning. RPGs, on the other hand, often allow players to continue from a save point or checkpoint. - Roguelikes generally have procedurally generated levels, meaning that each playthrough is different, while RPGs often have a fixed, pre-designed world and story. - RPGs are usually more story-driven than Roguelikes, with detailed plotlines, memorable characters, and extensive dialogue. - While turn-based combat is a staple of both genres, Roguelikes are more likely to be grid-based and designed around individual character movement and positioning during combat. RPGs may or may not feature grid-based combat but frequently include more complex, team-focused mechanics. - Character progression in Roguelikes is typically faster – reaching more advanced levels, abilities, and items more quickly – and the overall experience is usually more difficult and unforgiving. In contrast, RPGs tend to have more gradual character progression and more forgiving gameplay, though this can certainly vary between titles. - Roguelikes often have a more limited narrative scope, focusing more on gameplay and replayability than intricate storytelling. RPGs, on the other hand, may have branching storylines with multiple endings or deep moral choices for players to make. - Roguelikes are sometimes characterized by their ASCII-based or minimalist art styles, while RPGs often boast rich, detailed graphics and immersive game environments."},{"instruction":"It is 21:00 EST on May 6th, 2023 in Bridgeport, CT. When will it be time for Muslims to pray?","output":"To determine the exact prayer times for Muslims in Bridgeport, CT, on May 6th, 2023, specific information is needed, such as the longitude and latitude of the location and the angle of the sun on that specific day. However, I can provide you with general guidelines for approximate prayer times according to the five daily prayers in Islam: 1. Fajr (pre-dawn): This prayer is performed before sunrise. It starts when the sky begins to lighten (the dawn) and ends just before the sun rises. 2. Dhuhr (midday): This prayer is performed shortly after midday when the sun begins to decline from its zenith. 3. Asr (afternoon): This prayer is performed in the afternoon, generally when the shadow of an object is the same length as the object itself, plus the shadow it cast at the sun's zenith. 4. Maghrib (evening): This prayer is performed just after sunset when the sun has completely set, and the sky is getting darker. 5. Isha (night): This prayer is performed after the twilight has disappeared, and the sky is completely dark. To find the exact prayer times, you can check local prayer time tables, or use prayer time apps or we